 64→+# In-Game Mail Design
 65→+
 66→+Text-only mail for WoW 3.3.5a. No attachments, COD, or items in v1.
 67→+
 68→+## Mailbox GUID Requirement
 69→+
 70→+Every mail operation requires a valid mailbox GUID. The server validates that the player is near the referenced mailbox. We handle `SMSG_SHOW_MAILBOX` to capture the GUID when the player interacts with a mailbox (via NPC gossip, gameobject click, or playerbot command). Commands error with a clear message when no mailbox is open.
 71→+
 72→+## Commands
 73→+
 74→+| Input | Action |
 75→+|-------|--------|
 76→+| `/mail` | List inbox (sequential indices) |
 77→+| `/mail read <n>` | Show full mail, mark as read |
 78→+| `/mail send <player> "<subject>" <body>` | Send text-only mail |
 79→+| `/mail delete <n>` | Delete mail by index |
 80→+
 81→+Daemon IPC: `MAIL`, `MAIL_READ <n>`, `MAIL_SEND <player> "<subject>" <body>`, `MAIL_DELETE <n>`, plus `_JSON` variants for list/read.
 82→+
 83→+## Packets
 84→+
 85→+**Incoming:**
 86→+
 87→+- `SMSG_SHOW_MAILBOX` (0x297) — 8-byte mailbox GUID. Store on WorldConn, auto-request mail list.
 88→+- `SMSG_MAIL_LIST_RESULT` (0x23B) — u32 total count, u8 displayed count, then per-mail: u16 size, u32 messageId, u8 messageType, conditional sender (u64 GUID for player, u32 entry for NPC/auction), u32 cod, u32 unknown, u32 stationery, u32 money, u32 flags, f32 expirationTime, u32 templateId, cString subject, cString body, u8 itemCount. Skip remaining bytes per entry using the size field.
 89→+- `SMSG_SEND_MAIL_RESULT` (0x239) — u32 mailId, u32 action, u32 result. Map action+result to user-facing messages.
 90→+- `SMSG_RECEIVED_MAIL` (0x285) — Already handled. Shows "You have new mail."
 91→+
 92→+**Outgoing:**
 93→+
 94→+- `CMSG_GET_MAIL_LIST` (0x23A) — u64 mailboxGuid.
 95→+- `CMSG_SEND_MAIL` (0x238) — u64 mailboxGuid, cString receiver, cString subject, cString body, u32 stationery=0, u32 unknown=0, u8 items=0, u32 money=0, u32 cod=0, u32 unknown=0, u32 unknown=0.
 96→+- `CMSG_MAIL_DELETE` (0x249) — u64 mailboxGuid, u32 mailId, u32 templateId=0.
 97→+- `CMSG_MAIL_MARK_AS_READ` (0x247) — u64 mailboxGuid, u32 mailId.
 98→+
 99→+## State
100→+
101→+On WorldConn (not a separate store — mail state is simpler than guilds/friends):
102→+
103→+- `mailboxGuid: bigint | null` — set by SMSG_SHOW_MAILBOX, cleared on disconnect
104→+- `mailCache: MailEntry[]` — populated by SMSG_MAIL_LIST_RESULT
105→+
106→+## Display
107→+
108→+Inbox:
109→+```
110→+=== Mailbox (3 messages) ===
111→+ #1  Thrall         Guild meeting           2h
112→+ #2  Jaina          Hey there               1d
113→+*#3  Auction House  You won: [Hearthstone]  3d
114→+```
115→+`*` = unread. Columns: index, sender (padded), subject (truncated), relative time.
116→+
117→+Reading:
118→+```
119→+From: Thrall
120→+Subject: Guild meeting
121→+Date: 2h ago
122→+
123→+Don't forget about the raid tonight at 8pm. Bring flasks.
124→+```
125→+
126→+## Error Messages
127→+
128→+| Code | Message |
129→+|------|---------|
130→+| 2 | Cannot send mail to yourself. |
131→+| 3 | Not enough gold to send mail. |
132→+| 4 | Player not found. |
133→+| 5 | Cannot send mail to the opposite faction. |
134→+| 14 | Trial accounts cannot send mail. |
135→+| 15 | Recipient's mailbox is full. |
136→+| 17 | Mail is suspended on this account. |
137→+| Other | Mail error (code N). |
